# 🛠️ Tech Stack for Amane & Selamta (Web App)

## 🌐 Frontend
- Framework: Next.js (React-based, SSR, PWA-ready)
- Styling: Tailwind CSS (responsive, utility-first)
- State Management: Zustand or Context API
- Routing: Next.js App Router
- Icons: Lucide.dev (lightweight, SVG)

## 🖥️ Backend
- Server: Node.js + Express or Django (Python)
- Database: PostgreSQL (relational) or MongoDB (NoSQL)
- Auth: Firebase Auth or OAuth2 (optional)
- File Storage: Cloudinary or Supabase Storage
- Realtime: Socket.io or Firebase Realtime DB

## 📱 Mobile/Web Compatibility
- Responsive design with Flexbox/Grid
- PWA via Workbox (offline caching)
- Browser compatibility: Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge

## 🌍 Localization
- i18n: next-i18next (for multilingual support)
- Translations: Amharic, Oromo, Tigrinya, English
- Cultural notes in translations

## 🚀 Hosting & Deployment
- Frontend: Vercel (free tier, automatic deployments)
- Backend: Render or Railway (free tiers available)
- Domain: Custom domain (e.g., amane.et or selamta.et)

## 🧪 Testing & QA
- Unit Tests: Jest + React Testing Library
- E2E: Cypress or Playwright
- Accessibility: axe-core, Lighthouse
